# see.word — what SEE is: to perceive a fold, and change nothing.
# Axiom: bottoms out in the host (the SEE verb and the descriptor it returns). Descends from
# word.word, chain.word, fold.word. Every word grounded (see, fold, fact). This word DECLARES
# the verb. Who may see is a grant, held through `can`, declared later; the verb never grants.
# See makes no fact of the place: of the roots it is the only read, where do, be, and name write.
# A space may hold a role open to any who enter — that is the space's policy, a fact ON the space,
# not an act of the see. A being that wants the role reads the policy and takes it itself; the being
# acts, never the space, never the see. (A space is a noun; only a being acts.)
# To recall is a see of the past, and waits for the past views and `name`.

A see is a being's fold of the present.
A see makes no fact of the place.
